<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="1304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1304">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-10T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1916, 4 p. m</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1413. Department is informed from Rome that there is to be a conference
                            at Paris for closer commercial relations between the Allies, and that
                            efforts may be made to apply restrictions possibly affecting American
                            interests. Should this conference take place, endeavor to ascertain its
                            results, using every discretion in doing so.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>